At least five people, including two children and two women, drowned in India’s western state of Gujarat on Sunday evening after their boat capsized in a lake, according to a local policewoman on Monday. The dead bodies of the deceased were recovered and the rescue work was over. “There were 22 persons on board the boat when it capsized,’’ said the policewoman over the phone. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The mishap occurred in Gujarat’s Navsari district, at the lake which is a popular destination. The incident took place as the number of people aboard the ill-fated boat was more than its capacity.